# Plugin API Structure (McLib Pattern)

## Module Split

| Module | Contents |
|--------|----------|
| **`*-api`** | Interfaces, data classes, abstract types – no Bukkit/implementation details |
| **`*-plugin`** | Concrete implementations, Bukkit integration, listeners |

## Implementations in the Plugin Module

**All implementations of API interfaces must live under the `api` package/folder.**

```
plugin-module/
  src/.../bukkit/
    api/                    ← All API implementations (required)
      MicroGamesApiImpl.kt
      arena/
        ArenaContextImpl.kt
        ArenaManagerImpl.kt
      phase/
        DefaultPhaseProvider.kt
        InGamePhase.kt
        ...
    arena/                  ← Internal only (ArenaImpl, ArenaVisibilityController)
    phase/                  ← Empty – phases moved to api/phase/
    loader/
    MicroGamesPlugin.kt
```

## Rules

1. **API module**: Only interfaces, data classes, abstract types. No `implementation` of Bukkit/Paper.
2. **Plugin module**: Every class that implements an API interface goes in `.../bukkit/api/` (or subpackages like `api/arena/`, `api/phase/`).
3. **Provider pattern**: If the plugin exposes its own API, use `XxxProvider.api` analogous to McLib.
4. **Plugin class**: Sets `Provider.api = ApiImpl(...)` on startup and uses the implementations.
